{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778378769446,"sessionID":"ses_1f064d1bcffeSfMahBCSBq7Tqb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1cloQnIW4oelRLQA9L86Nuox","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19000915.md","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19000915.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:19000915\n3: title: \"BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\"\n4: authors:\n5: - Gomes MS\n6: - Mendes MM\n7: - de Oliveira F\n8: - de Andrade RM\n9: - Bernardes CP\n10: - Hamaguchi A\n11: - de Alcântara TM\n12: - Soares AM\n13: - Rodrigues VM\n14: - Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\n15: journal: Toxicon\n16: year: '2009'\n17: doi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\n18: keywords:\n19: - Animals\n20: - Bothrops/physiology\n21: - Crotalid Venoms/enzymology\n22: - \"Dose-Response Relationship, Drug\"\n23: - Edema/chemically induced\n24: - Hemorrhage/chemically induced\n25: - Hindlimb\n26: - Male\n27: - \"Metalloproteases/chemistry, metabolism\"\n28: - Mice\n29: - \"Muscle, Skeletal/drug effects, pathology\"\n30: content_type: abstract_only\n31: ---\n32: \n33: # BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\n34: **Authors:** Gomes MS, Mendes MM, de Oliveira F, de Andrade RM, Bernardes CP, Hamaguchi A, de Alcântara TM, Soares AM, Rodrigues VM, Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\n35: **Journal:** Toxicon (2009)\n36: **DOI:** [10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007)\n37: \n38: ## Content\n39: \n40: 1. Toxicon. 2009 Jan;53(1):24-32. doi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007. Epub 2008\n41: Oct  17.\n42: \n43: BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake \n44: venom.\n45: \n46: Gomes MS(1), Mendes MM, de Oliveira F, de Andrade RM, Bernardes CP, Hamaguchi A, \n47: de Alcântara TM, Soares AM, Rodrigues VM, Homsi-Brandeburgo MI.\n48: \n49: Author information:\n50: (1)Instituto de Genética e Bioquímica, Universidade Federal de Uberlândia (UFU), \n51: 38400-902 Uberlândia-MG, Brazil. mrochauesb@yahoo.com.br\n52: \n53: In this work, a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase (BthMP) was purified \n54: from Bothrops moojeni snake venom. This enzyme was homogeneous by native and \n55: SDS-PAGE. It showed a polypeptide chain of 23.5kDa, pI=7.1, and N-terminal \n56: blocked. BthMP is comprised of high proteolytic activity on casein, fibrin and \n57: bovine fibrinogen, with no coagulating, esterase or phospholipase A(2) \n58: activities; it was inhibited by EDTA, EGTA and 1,10-phenanthroline and \n59: maintained its activity on pH from 7.0 to 9.0 and temperature from 5-40 degrees \n60: C. Assays with metal ions showed that Ca(2+) is an activator, whereas Zn(2+) and \n61: Hg(2+) inhibited about 50 and 80% of its activity, respectively. The edema \n62: evidenced the important role of the toxin in the inflammatory activity of the \n63: venom. BthMP also caused unclotting, and provoked histological alterations in \n64: the gastrocnemius muscle of mice inducing hemorrhage, necrosis and leukocytic \n65: infiltrate. The molecular mass and the inhibition assays suggest that the \n66: metalloproteinase BthMP belongs to class P-I of SVMPs.\n67: \n68: DOI: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\n69: PMID: 19000915 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:19000915\ntitle: \"BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\"\nauthors:\n- Gomes MS\n- Mendes MM\n- de Oliveira F\n- de Andrade RM\n- Bernardes CP\n- Hamaguchi A\n- de Alcântara TM\n- Soares AM\n- Rodrigues VM\n- Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\njournal: Toxicon\nyear: '2009'\ndoi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Bothrops/physiology","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_1900091