eakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom\n\n[Mário Sérgio R Gomes](/?term=Gomes+MS&cauthor_id=19000915)  [1](#full-view-affiliation-1 \"Instituto de Genética e Bioquímica, Universidade Federal de Uberlândia (UFU), 38400-902 Uberlândia-MG, Brazil. mrochauesb@yahoo.com.br\") , [Mirian M Mendes](/?term=Mendes+MM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Fábio de Oliveira](/?term=de+Oliveira+F&cauthor_id=19000915), [Rodrigo M de Andrade](/?term=de+Andrade+RM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Carolina P Bernardes](/?term=Bernardes+CP&cauthor_id=19000915), [Amélia Hamaguchi](/?term=Hamaguchi+A&cauthor_id=19000915), [Tânia M de Alcântara](/?term=de+Alc%C3%A2ntara+TM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Andreimar M Soares](/?term=Soares+AM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Veridiana M Rodrigues](/?term=Rodrigues+VM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Maria I Homsi-Brandeburgo](/?term=Homsi-Brandeburgo+MI&cauthor_id=19000915)\n\nAffiliations Expand\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Instituto de Genética e Bioquímica, Universidade Federal de Uberlândia (UFU), 38400-902 Uberlândia-MG, Brazil. mrochauesb@yahoo.com.br\n\n-   PMID: **19000915**\n-   DOI: [10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\n# BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom\n\nMário Sérgio R Gomes et al. Toxicon. 2009 Jan.\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nToxicon\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Toxicon%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22Toxicon%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2009 Jan;53(1):24-32.\n\ndoi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007. Epub 2008 Oct 17.\n\n### Authors\n\n[Mário Sérgio R Gomes](/?term=Gomes+MS&cauthor_id=19000915)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Instituto de Genética e Bioquímica, Universidade Federal de Uberlândia (UFU), 38400-902 Uberlândia-MG, Brazil. mrochauesb@yahoo.com.br\") , [Mirian M Mendes](/?term=Mendes+MM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Fábio de Oliveira](/?term=de+Oliveira+F&cauthor_id=19000915), [Rodrigo M de Andrade](/?term=de+Andrade+RM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Carolina P Bernardes](/?term=Bernardes+CP&cauthor_id=19000915), [Amélia Hamaguchi](/?term=Hamaguchi+A&cauthor_id=19000915), [Tânia M de Alcântara](/?term=de+Alc%C3%A2ntara+TM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Andreimar M Soares](/?term=Soares+AM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Veridiana M Rodrigues](/?term=Rodrigues+VM&cauthor_id=19000915), [Maria I Homsi-Brandeburgo](/?term=Homsi-Brandeburgo+MI&cauthor_id=19000915)\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Instituto de Genética e Bioquímica, Universidade Federal de Uberlândia (UFU), 38400-902 Uberlândia-MG, Brazil. mrochauesb@yahoo.com.br\n\n-   PMID: **19000915**\n-   DOI: [10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\nIn this work, a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase (BthMP) was purified from Bothrops moojeni snake venom. This enzyme was homogeneous by native and SDS-PAGE. It showed a polypeptide chain of 23.5kDa, pI=7.1, and N-terminal blocked. BthMP is comprised of high proteolytic activity on casein, fibrin and bovine fibrinogen, with no coagulating, esterase or phospholipase A(2) activities; it was inhibited by EDTA, EGTA and 1,10-phenanthroline and maintained its activity on pH from 7.0 to 9.0 and temperature from 5-40 degrees C. Assays with metal ions showed that Ca(2+) is an activator, whereas Zn(2+) and Hg(2+) inhibited about 50 and 80% of its activity, respectively. The edema evidenced the important role of the toxin in the inflammatory activity of the venom. BthMP also caused unclotting, and provoked histological alterations in the gastrocnemius muscle of mice inducing hemorrhage, necrosis and leukocytic infiltrate. The molecular mass and the inhibition assays suggest that the metalloproteinase BthMP belongs to class P-I of SVMPs.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## Publication types\n\n-   Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t%22%5Bpt%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n\n## MeSH terms\n\n-   Animals\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Animals%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Animals)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Bothrops / physiology\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Bothrops%2Fphysiology%22%5BMAJR%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Bothrops)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Crotalid Venoms / enzymology\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Crotalid+Venoms%2Fenzymology%22%5BMAJR%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Crotalid+Venoms)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Dose-Response Relationship, Drug\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Dose-Response+Relationship%2C+Drug%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Dose-Response+Relationship%2C+Drug)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Edema / chemically induced\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Edema%2Fchemically+induced%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Edema)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Hemorrhage / chemically induced\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Hemorrhage%2Fchemically+induced%22%5BMAJR%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   