{"type":"text","timestamp":1778378798809,"sessionID":"ses_1f064d1bcffeSfMahBCSBq7Tqb","part":{"id":"prt_e0fa2f29f001QRdXDDN4WM3XIB","messageID":"msg_e0fa2d684001R57l6XioDieHb7","sessionID":"ses_1f064d1bcffeSfMahBCSBq7Tqb","type":"text","text":"I’ll add the new term as a compositional venom-mediated positive regulation term, following existing `venom-mediated activation of ...` precedents with `positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006954`. The temporary research and design notes will remain uncommitted.","time":{"start":1778378797727,"end":1778378798808},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e549f06239976910169ffe82db4108192bc0c806156612a85","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778378813851,"sessionID":"ses_1f064d1bcffeSfMahBCSBq7Tqb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_TJwvA851Qm2XBZiWEi8jrOI2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: RESEARCH.md\n+# Research for issue #31902\n+\n+## PMID:32024243 \"Inflammatory Reaction Induced by Two Metalloproteinases Isolated from Bothrops atrox Venom and by Fragments Generated from the Hydrolysis of Basement Membrane Components\"\n+\n+This paper directly supports venom metalloproteinase-driven inflammatory reactions, including edema, leukocyte accumulation, and release of inflammatory mediators. PubMed metadata confirmed PMID:32024243, PMCID:PMC7076977, DOI:10.3390/toxins12020096.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:32024243 \"Both SVMPs induced edema, representing an increase of ~70% of the paw size. Leukocyte infiltrates reached levels of 6 × 106 with ATXL and 5 × 106 with BATXH. TNF-α was identified in the supernatant of BATXH-or venom-stimulated MPAC cells.\"\n+  - Supports venom metalloproteinase-mediated induction of inflammatory phenotypes, including edema, leukocyte infiltration, and inflammatory mediator release.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:32024243 \"Our findings suggest that ATXL and BATXH are involved in the inflammatory reaction observed in B. atrox envenomings by direct action on inflammatory cells or by releasing proinflammatory peptides from BM proteins that may amplify the direct action of SVMPs through activation of endogenous signaling pathways.\"\n+  - Supports the requested parent concept of venom-mediated activation of inflammatory response.\n+\n+## PMID:19000915 \"BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom\"\n+\n+This paper supports inflammatory effects of a snake venom metalloproteinase, including edema and leukocytic infiltrate. Metadata were cached with `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:19000915`; DOI:10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19000915 \"The edema evidenced the important role of the toxin in the inflammatory activity of the venom. BthMP also caused unclotting, and provoked histological alterations in the gastrocnemius muscle of mice inducing hemorrhage, necrosis and leukocytic infiltrate.\"\n+  - Supports snake venom metalloproteinase involvement in inflammatory activity, including edema and leukocyte infiltration.\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design patterns for issue #31902\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+Create `venom-mediated activation of inflammatory response` as a biological process term under `GO:0035738 venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`.\n+\n+## Existing GO pattern precedent\n+\n+The general GO positive regulation pattern (`src/design_patterns/positive_regulation.yaml`) defines terms of the form `positive regulation of %s` with logical definition `GO:0065007 biological regulation` plus `positively_regulates` some target process.\n+\n+For venom-mediated biological process perturbation terms, existing GO terms use a specialized precedent rather than the generic positive regulation genus:\n+\n+* `GO:0044480 venom-mediated mast cell degranulation`\n+  * `intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+  * `intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0043303 ! mast cell degranulation`\n+* `GO:0044494 venom-mediated activation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity`\n+  * `intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+  * `intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0005248 ! voltage-gated sodium channel activity`\n+* `GO:0044514 venom-mediated activation of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway`\n+  * `intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+  * `intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007186 ! G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway`\n+\n+## Design decision\n+\n+Use the existing venom-mediated activation pattern:\n+\n+* Genus: `GO:0035738 venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+* Differentia: `positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006954 inflammatory response`\n+* Definition style: `A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances ... in another organism via the action of a venom.`\n+\n+The existing pattern implies the requested subclass relationship to `GO:0035738`; no extra asserted `is_a` is needed.\n*** Add File: terms/GO_7770071.obo\n+[Term]\n+id: GO:7770071\n+name: venom-mediated activation of inflammatory response\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances an inflammatory response in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:19000915, PMID:32024243]\n+synonym: \"venom-mediated inflammation\" BROAD []\n+intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\n+intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31902\" xsd:anyURI\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+creation_date: 2026-05-10T02:06:30Z\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA terms/GO_7770071.obo","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@\n+# Research for issue #31902\n+\n+## PMID:32024243 \"Inflammatory Reaction Induced by Two Metalloproteinases Isolated from Bothrops atrox Venom and by Fragments Generated from the Hydrolysis of Basement Membrane Components\"\n+\n+This paper directly supports venom metalloproteinase-driven inflammatory reactions, including edema, leukocyte accumulation, and release of inflammatory mediators. PubMed metadata confirmed PMID:32024243, PMCID:PMC7076977, DOI:10.3390/toxins12020096.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:32024243 \"Both SVMPs induced edema, representing an increase of ~70% of the paw size. Leukocyte infiltrates reached levels of 6 × 106 with ATXL and 5 × 106 with BATXH. TNF-α was identified in the supernatant of BATXH-or venom-stimulated MPAC cells.\"\n+  - Supports venom metalloproteinase-mediated induction of inflammatory phenotypes, including edema, leukocyte infiltration, and inflammatory mediator release.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:32024243 \"Our findings suggest that ATXL and BATXH are involved in the inflammatory reaction observed in B. atrox envenomings by direct action on inflammatory cells or by releasing proinflammatory peptides from BM proteins that may amplify the direct action of SVMPs through activation of endogenous signaling pathways.\"\n+  - Supports the requested parent concept of venom-mediated activation of inflammatory response.\n+\n+## PMID:19000915 \"BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom\"\n+\n+This paper supports inflammatory effects of a snake venom metalloproteinase, including edema and leukocytic infiltrate. Metadata were cached with `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:19000915`; DOI:10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19000915 \"The edema evidenced the important role of the toxin in the inflammatory activity of the venom. BthMP also caused unclotting, and provoked histological alterations in the gastrocnemius muscle of mice inducing hemorrhage, necrosis and leukocytic infiltrate.\"\n+  - Supports snake venom metalloproteinase involvement in inflammatory activity, including edema and leukocyte infiltration.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+# Design patterns for issue #31902\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+Create `venom-mediated activation of inflammatory response` as a biological process term under `GO:0035738 venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`.\n+\n+## Existing GO pattern precedent\n+\n+The general GO positive regulation pattern (`src/design_patterns/positive_regulation.yaml`) defines terms of the form `positive regulation of %s` with logical definition `GO:0065007 biological regulation` plus `positively_regulates` some target process.\n+\n+For venom-mediated biological process perturbation terms, existing GO terms use a specialized precedent rather than the generic positive regulation genus:\n+\n+* `GO:0044480 venom-mediated mast cell degranulation`\n+  * `intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+  * `intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0043303 ! mast cell degranulation`\n+* `GO:0044494 venom-mediated activation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity`\n+  * `intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+  * `intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0005248 ! voltage-gated sodium channel activity`\n+* `GO:0044514 venom-mediated activation of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway`\n+  * `intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+  * `intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007186 ! G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway`\n+\n+## Design decision\n+\n+Use the existing venom-mediated activation pattern:\n+\n+* Genus: `GO:0035738 venom-mediated perturbation of biological process`\n+* Differentia: `positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006954 inflammatory response`\n+* Definition style: `A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances ... in another organism via the action of a venom.`\n+\n+The existing pattern implies the requested subclass relationship to `GO:0035738`; no extra asserted `is_a` is needed.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770071.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770071.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770071.obo\n@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@\n+[Term]\n+id: GO:7770071\n+name: venom-mediated activation of inflammatory response\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances an inflammatory response in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:19000915, PMID:32024243]\n+synonym: \"venom-mediated inflammation\" BROAD []\n+intersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\n+intersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006954 ! inflammatory response\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31902\" xsd:anyURI\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+creation_date: 2026-05-10T02:06:30Z\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md","relativePath":"RESEARCH.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@\n+# Research for issue #31902\n+\n+## PMID:32024243 \"Inflammatory Reaction Induced by Two Metalloproteinases Isolated from Bothrops atrox Venom and by Fragments Generated from the Hydrolysis of Basement Membrane Components\"\n+\n+This paper directly supports venom metalloproteinase-driven inflammatory reactions, including edema, leukocyte accumulation, and release of inflammatory mediators. PubMed metadata confirmed PMID:32024243, PMCID:PMC7076977, DOI:10.3390/toxins12020096.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:32024243 \"Both SVMPs induced edema